message.content:
A 'Papilio machaon' is a species of butterfly commonly known as the Old World swallowtail.
It has a wingspan of approximately 65-86 millimeters.
The upper side of its wings are yellow with black markings while the hindwings have blue markings.
The underside of the hindwings have a distinctive red spot surrounded by blue crescents.
The body of the butterfly is slender and have a black and yellow striped pattern.
It can be found in the temperate and tropical regions of Europe and Asia.
The 'Papilio machaon' feeds on nectar from a variety of flowers and its larvae feed on plants in the carrot family.
